cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.IR 

The paper deals with the application of deep convolutional neural networks (DCN) for abnormality detection and localization in chest X-rays. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of DCN for medical image diagnosis also involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. Additionally, the paper deals with medical imaging (cs.MED) and information retrieval (cs.IR) as it involves the classification and localization of abnormalities in medical images.
